fg_segments: Privacy Policy, Terms of Service & Copyrights Governing SentinelSource.comWe do not require registration on SentinelSource.com
You can visit many pages on our site without providing any information.
Other pages may prompt you to enter information, such as a user name and password, before you can access the information.

When registering or participating in interactive or subscription areas of our site, we may ask for certain demographic information, such as age, income level, zip code, number of household members, and the like.

This information is gathered for use by Keene Publishing and SentinelSource to help us understand and more closely identify our users and readers so that we may continue to improve, enhance or add new features and services that may appeal to our customers.
Keene Publishing does not share any identifying information with third parties without a reader's knowledge & consent.
From time to time you may receive promotional information from Keene Publishing, such as invitations to participate in contests, user polls, subscription offers, and advertising promotions.

If you do not want to receive promotional information from Keene Publishing, please notify the Interactive Media Department at webmaster@keenesentinel.comKeene Publishing Copyright NoticeAll information, content, services and software displayed on, transmitted through, or used in connection with SentinelSource, including for example materials such as writings, software, music, works of art, graphics, logos, trademarks, photographs, and the like (hereafter referred to as "Content"), as well as the selection and arrangement of content is owned by Keene Publishing Corporation.

You may use the Content online only, and solely for your personal, non-commercial use, and you may download or print a single copy of any portion of the Content solely for your personal non-commercial use, provided you do not remove any trademark, copyright or other notice from such Content.
If you operate a Web site and wish to link to SentinelSource.com, you may do so provided you agree to cease such link upon request from SentinelSource.com.
No other use is permitted without prior written permission of SentinelSource.com.
Use of this site is described in the TERMS of SERVICE section of this page.
Prohibited UsesSentinelSource.com is not intended for use by persons located within the European Economic Area (EEA).

SentinelSource and Keene Publishing Corporation do not request or accept personal information concerning or supplied by persons who are located within the EEA at the time they access SentinelSource.com.
If you have accessed SentinelSource.com from within the EEA, you should immediately discontinue your use.

If you have supplied personal information to us in violation of this provision, whether through the registration of new user accounts or otherwise, please contact us at webmaster@keenesentinel.com.Terms of ServiceSubscriptions and Archive Accounts (Membership)If you become a Member of SentinelSource.com you accept responsibility for all activities that occur under your account or password, and agree not to sell, transfer or assign your membership rights.
We reserve the right to terminate your Membership if individuals from more than one household access SentinelSource using any single user name or password.

You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your password and for restricting access to your computer so others outside your household may not access SentinelSource.com using your name in whole or in part without our permission.

If you believe that someone has accessed SentinelSource.com using your user name and password without your authorization, please email us immediately at one of the following addresses: webmaster@keenesentinel.com or circulation@keenesentinel.comUser-Provided Information and ContentBy providing information to, communicating with, and/or placing material on, SentinelSource.com, including for example, communication during registration, communication on any SentinelSource forum area, photo gallery submissions, reader's arena, movie reviews, photos or other content, or entering any contests, you represent and warrant:1) you own or otherwise have all necessary rights to the content you provide and the rights to use it as provided in this TERMS of SERVICE;2) all information you provide is true, accurate, current and complete, and does not violate these TERMS of SERVICE;3) the content will not cause injury to any person or entity.
Using a name other than your own legal name is prohibited, except in specific areas of SentinelSource where unique names are commonly used, such as login or user names.

For all such information and material, you grant Keene Publishing a royalty-free, perpetual, irrevocable, non-exclusive right and license to use, copy, modify, display, archive, store, distribute, reproduce and create derivative works from such information, in any form, of any kind now existing or developed in the future.

You also grant Keene Publishing the right to use any material, information, ideas, concepts, know-how or techniques contained in any communication you send to us for any purpose whatsoever, including but not limited to developing, manufacturing and marketing products using such information.
All rights in this paragraph are granted without the need for any compensation of any sort to you.
Please note that Keene Publishing does not accept unsolicited materials or ideas for use or publication and is not responsible for the similarity of any of its content or programming.

Should you send any unsolicited materials or ideas, you do so with the understanding no consideration of any sort will be provided to you, and you are waiving any claim against Keene Publishing Corporation, SentinelSource.com and their affiliated publications and Web sites regarding the use of such materials and ideas, even if material or an idea is used that is substantially similar to the idea you sent.

Transactions and EcommerceDuring your visit to our site you may elect to engage in a transaction involving the purchase of a product or service such as a newspaper subscription, a print or online advertisement or other tangible goods and services.
To serve you most efficiently, credit card transactions and order fulfillment are often handled by a third party processing agent, bank or distribution institution.
Keene Publishing and its vendors make every effort to ensure secure transactions through the use of encrypted security software.
While in most cases transactions are completed without difficulty, there is no such thing as "perfect security" on the Internet or offline.
If you're concerned about online credit card safety, in most cases a telephone number will be made available so you can call us and place your order by phone.
SentinelSource.com cannot take responsibility for the success or security of transactions undertaken or processed by third parties.
On occasion, a product or service may not be available at the time or the price as it appears in an advertisement.

In such event, or in the event a product is listed at an incorrect price or with incorrect information due to typographical error, technology effort, error in the date or length of publication, or error in pricing or product information received from our advertisers or suppliers, you agree SentinelSource.com is not responsible for such errors or discrepancies.

Subscription Refund PolicyYour newspaper delivery service may continue past your subscription renewal date unless you notify the Circulation Department in advance to stop your subscription upon expire.
All credit balance amounts remaining upon subscription stop date will be returned, upon request, typically within 2- 4 weeks.
The Circulation Department can be reached at 603-352-1234 ext.
1300.Posting Rules and InteractivityInteractive areas, discussion forums, and reader submitted content areas, are intended to encourage an exchange of ideas and opinions.
These areas are offered to all users of the site.
Keene Publishing reserves the right to refuse to post any content on our site at any time, for any reason.
Decisions as to whether content violates any Posting Rule will be made by Keene Publishing in its discretion.
All content submitted for posting is reviewed by SentinelSource staff before publication on our site.
Be aware that submitted content may be edited by SentinelSource staff for space considerations at Keene Publishing's sole discretion.
Any submitted content, including, but not limited to the type described below, is subject to being edited or refused.
If repeated violations occur, Keene Publishing reserves the right to cancel user access to SentinelSource without advanced notice.

When submitting content to SentinelSource, please do not submit content that:contains vulgar, profane, abusive, racist or hateful language or expressions, epithets or slurs, text, photographs or illustrations in poor taste, inflammatory attacks of a personal, racial or religious nature.is defamatory, threatening, disparaging, grossly inflammatory, false, misleading, fraudulent, inaccurate, unfair, contains gross exaggeration or unsubstantiated claims, violates the privacy rights of any third party, is unreasonably harmful or offensive to any individual or community.violates any right of SentinelSource.com or any third party.discriminates on the grounds of race, religion, national origin, gender, age, marital status, sexual orientation or disability, or refers to such matters in any manner prohibited by law.violates or inappropriately encourages the violation of any municipal, state, federal or international law, rule, regulation or ordinance.unfairly interferes with any third party's uninterrupted use of SentinelSource.com.advertises, promotes or offers to trade any goods or services, except in areas specifically designated for such purpose.uploads copyrighted or other proprietary material of any kind on SentinelSource.com without the express permission of the owner of that material.uses or attempts to use another's account, password, service or system except as expressly permitted by the Terms of Service.uploads or transmits viruses or other harmful, disruptive or destructive files.disrupts, interferes with, or otherwise harms or violates the security of SentinelSource.com or any services, system resources, accounts, passwords, servers or networks connected to or accessible through SentinelSource.com or affiliated or linked sites.sends repeated messages related to another user and/or makes derogatory or offensive comments about another individual or repeats prior posting of the same message under multiple emails or subjects.

Ecommerce Submissions or Submissions to third parties:Your communication with any other party through SentinelSource, including advertisers, for the purpose of communication or transactions, are solely between you and that third party.
For example, certain areas of SentinelSource may offer links to other businesses or ecommerce transactions with that third party.
Under no circumstances will Keene Publishing be liable for any goods, services, resources or content available through such third party dealings or communications.

Please review carefully that third party's policies and practices and make sure you are comfortable with them before you engage in any transaction, Complaints concerns or questions relating to materials provided by third parties should be forwarded directly to the third party.

General Information:Keene Publishing may modify, suspend or discontinue or restrict the use of any portion of SentinelSource.com, including the availability of content at any time, without notice or liability.
Keene Publishing may deny access to the any person or user at any time for any reason.
Keene Publishing reserves the right to transfer the rights and obligations of any user or reader at any time for any reason.
